Yogourt parfaits can be great fuel for your body and brain as they're usually loaded with nutrients such as protein, fibre, natural sugars, and healthy fats that help you move throughout the day A parfait is a rich cold dessert that draws its origin from France. It usually has a rich pâté and a very smooth consistency. Parfaits are made by boiling cream, egg, sugar and syrup to create a custard-like puree. However, the recipe can be customized and other things added to enhance the richness of the dessert and appease ones taste buds. This sweet dessert is mouth-watering delicious no wonder its French name appropriately translates to "perfect." Ingredients Method Combine yogourt, ice cream, orange rind and half the sugar in a bowl. Combine berries in a bowl, using a fork lightly crush them then stir in remaining sugar. Layer yogourt mixture and crushed berries in large glass bowl. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes serve the garnish with toppings of choice. Enjoy